[38;5;141m> [0mI notice a minor grammar issue on line 9: "One image, one page, a handful of fields, result in under three seconds." The subject is "One image, one page, a handful of fields" which is a list serving as the subject describing the process, but "result" should be "results" (or the sentence could be restructured). Actually, re-reading this, I think the intended reading is a series of characteristics listing what the insurance card scan involved, with "result in under three seconds" as the verb phrase. But "One image, one page, a handful of fields" is a compound subject where the last item governs the verb. Actually this sentence is meant as a shorthand list: "[It's] one image, one page, a handful of fields, [the] result [comes] in under three seconds." This is an intentional stylistic fragment listing characteristics. It reads fine as-is in the conversational style.[0m[0m
